				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=392303&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182932" alt="Voct" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=392303)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;" >Voct</a></span> <span class="odate time_1299940164 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Mar 2011 14:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1046654">
									

<p>If this thing only activates when motor vehicles are present, and specifically does <em>not</em> activate for pedestrians…</p>
<p>what happens if we send out a big bunch of pedestrians, have them stand a few paces apart all the way down the road, and <em>then</em> send out a car?</p>
<p>Or what if we send out a very <em>slow</em> motor vehicle, slow enough that a human can keep pace with it the whole time?</p>
<p>What if we drill a hole in the gas tank so that the car runs out of fuel and can't enter any of the challenges? What if we build a car that operates on beamed power, and then cut the power?</p>
<p>Pretty obvious that bicycles wouldn't activate this… <em>are</em> horse-drawn carriages safe?</p>
<p>What if we secretly program the car with the route so that it drives itself, and the steering wheel is a placebo?</p>

